== Ubuzima bwambere nuburere ==
Diarra yavutse mu 1955 i Segou, muri [[Mali]]  ariko aba impfubyi akiri muto kandi arerwa na nyirarume na nyirakuru. Mu 1975, yinjiye mu kigo cy’igihugu gishinzwe uburezi cya Diplome y’ubushakashatsi bwibanze (DEF) mu mwuga wo kwigisha. Nyuma yo guhindura siporo, hagati ya 1975 na 1977 yakiniye ikipe ya basketball ya Bamako Reds. Mu 1981, yabonye impamyabumenyi mu buhanzi bw'ikinamico mu kigo cy'igihugu gishinzwe ubuhanzi (INA). <ref>https://maliactu.net/mali-que-sont-ils-devenus-maimouna-helene-diarra-sous-les-vivats-de-la-rue-publique/</ref>

== Umwuga ==
Mu 2000, yagaragaye nka "Aminate" muri firime yikinamico ya Michael Haneke, ''Code Unknown'' . Abandi bakinnyi barimo:  Aïssa Maïga, Juliette Binoche, Thierry Neuvic, Josef Bierbichler n'abandi. <ref name="CUDb">https://m.imdb.com/title/tt0216625/?ref_=m_nm_knf_i1</ref>

Mu 2004, yagaragaye muri filime y'ururimi rwa Bambara ya Ousmane Sembène , Moolaadé, akina nka "Hadjatou". <ref>https://www.planocritico.com/critica-moolaade/</ref> <ref>https://www.albany.edu/writers-inst/webpages4/archives/cfseries/cfs28.html</ref> Abandi bakinnyi barimo: Fatoumata Coulibaly na Salimata Traoré. Filime yerekanwe muri Ebertfest 2007. <ref>https://editorial.rottentomatoes.com/guide/roger-eberts-great-movies/</ref> Yatorewe igihembo cya "Filime Nziza" mu iserukiramuco rya sinema rya Cannes . <ref>https://m.filmaffinity.com/us/awards-history.php?award_id=cannes&cat_id=un_certain_regard_best_film</ref>

Mu 2006, yakinnye muri filime y’ikinamico ya Abderrahmane Sissako, Bamako (film), aho yakinnye nka "Saramba". <ref name="Bam">https://m.imdb.com/title/tt0814666/?ref_=m_nm_knf_act_i3</ref> <ref>https://m.chicagoreader.com/chicago/bamako/Film?oid=5779914</ref> Abandi bakinnyi bagaragaye barimo: Aïssa Maïga na Tiécoura Traoré . <ref>https://catalog.afi.com/Catalog/moviedetails/64149</ref> <ref>https://geekvibesnation.com/art-house-cinema-streaming-platform-ovid-tv-announces-november-release-slate/</ref> <ref>http://www.frenchfilmfestival-archives.us/wp-content/archives_festivals/2007/bamako.html</ref>
